Cervino is a comune (municipality) in the Province of Caserta in the Italian region Campania, located about 30km northeast of Naples and about 7km east of Caserta. As of 31 December 2004, it had a population of 5,137 and an area of 8.0km.[1] Cervino borders the following municipalities: Durazzano, Maddaloni, Santa Maria a Vico, Valle di Maddaloni. [IMG]  
